[3
Date: 28 Feb 2001
From: Chris Griot <griot@freesurf.ch>
Source: MAFF

Vaccination dilemma
-------------------
The government is not now ruling out a vaccination program for Foot and
Mouth Disease. The advice of its veterinary chief is still against
vaccination. Agriculture minister in the Lords Hayman explained, "The use
of the vaccine means you compromise fatally your 'disease free' status,
because it is impossible to distinguish between animals having antibodies
because of vaccination and animals having antibodies because of disease.
And therefore there are enormous trade ramifications."
-足
Dr. C. Griot, DVM, PhD
Institute of Virology & Immunoprophylaxis,
National Reference Laboratory for Veterinary Diseases,
Swiss Federal Veterinary Institute,
Mittelhusern, SWITZERLAND
<griot@freesurf.ch>
