[4
Date: 28 Feb 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: BBC News, 28 Feb 2001 [edited

Thousands of cattle are being burnt at farms across the country. Desperate
farmers are inundating a helpline as fears about the impact of Foot and
Mouth Disease (FMD) grow. Experts are afraid this latest farming crisis
could be the last straw for many, leading to an even higher suicide rate in
the farming community.
Suicide rates are high, with 79 farm owners and managers, horticulturists
and farm workers in England and Wales killing themselves in 1999. The
helpline had received a number of calls from farmer's wives worried about
the mental health of their sons and husbands.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org
